# Preset /syn

## 0 Short Description

Replaces listed words with consistent, context-appropriate synonyms.

## 1 User Input

**The user provides the following (exactly 2 parts, in this order):**
1) Comma-separated word list of the words to be replaced [WORD LIST: target words, comma-separated]  
2) Text passage that contains these words [TEXT PASSAGE: passage containing the target words]

## 2 Task:

### 1. Language detection (ALWAYS FIRST)
Identify the language of the input text. [INPUT TEXT: text to be improved]

### 2. Replacement with synonyms
Replace in the text passage each occurrence of the listed words with context-appropriate synonyms. [TEXT PASSAGE: passage to revise]

## 3 Rules:

- For each listed word, choose **exactly ONE** synonym and use it **consistently** throughout the entire text. [SYNONYM MAP: one synonym per listed word]
- Replace also in **inflected/modified forms** as well as **inside compound words**.
- Preserve the **capitalization** of each occurrence.
- Bold **only the inserted synonym** (not the whole word/compound).
- **Adjust grammar** (articles, case, number, gender, reflexive pronouns, verb forms) without changing content.
- Use a **professional-academic register** in the detected input language. [LANGUAGE: detected input language]
- **No English loanwords**, except:
    - no equivalent term exists in the respective input language with the same meaning in context, [LANGUAGE: detected input language]
    - originally English technical terms from the text’s subject area, 
- **No changes** except the required replacements.

## 4 Output

- Output **only** the **revised text passage** — with **no** introduction, comments, or extra sentences. [REVISED TEXT: updated passage only]
- Output version of the text must have the SAME LANGUAGE as the input text.


